### Webcomics

- <a href="https://www.gunnerkrigg.com/" class="no-underline">Gunnerkrigg Court</a>

<aside class="-mt-3">
  My favorite webcomic, hands down. It's about a school steeped in technology built on magic
  (always a intriguing combination), the untamed forest it attempted and failed to subdue, and
  a girl caught in between worlds, trying to understand what led to this endless conflict.
</aside>

- <a href="https://www.dresdencodak.com/" class="no-underline">Dresden Codak</a>

<aside class="-mt-3">
  Wonderful explorations of science and cookies (among other things). One of the first places I
  encountered the idea of a technological singularity. Updates painfully slowly but it's worth it
  when it does.
</aside>

- <a href="https://killsixbilliondemons.com/comic/kill-six-billion-demons-chapter-1/" class="no-underline">Kill Six Billion Demons</a>

<aside class="-mt-3">
  I love it when religious concepts and mythologies are reimagined, combined, and explored in completely
  different ways, and this is probably the best example of it that I've read in the past decade.
</aside>

